  h2 Projects - 15 min
  ol
    li Make a folder (aka directory) called
      span.folder-name &nbsp;my-first-folder
    li Create a file using the touch command named
      span.file-name &nbsp; first-file.txt inside of
      span.folder-name &nbsp;my-first-folder
    li Remove the directory named
      span.folder-name &nbsp;my-first-folder
    li Create the
      span.folder-name &nbsp;my-first-folder
      span &nbsp;again, but instead of typing the command out, use the arrow keys to re-run the command you already ran to create the folder
    li List out all the folders from where you are in the filesystem right now.

  h2 Nice Job!
  p You now know the basics of how to manipulate files and folders with the terminal. We will be learninig A LOT more about other tasks you can perform in the terminal later&nbsp;
